Former Transnet engineer Francis Callard is continuing his testimony today, at the State of Capture Inquiry. Editor's note: Livestream courtesy DStv 403, you can also watch it on DStv Now. JOHANNESBURG - Former Transnet engineer Francis Callard is continuing his testimony on Monday at the State of Capture Inquiry. Last week, Callard testified that he had warned the parastatal, against signing a locomotives contract with China South Rail. Callard says his advice was ignored, and Transnet lost nearly R4-billion as a result.